<MemberDefinition
  prototype="const BitVector llvm::CriticalAntiDepBreaker::AllocatableSet">
The set of allocatable registers.

We&#39;ll be ignoring anti-dependencies on non-allocatable registers, because they may not be safe to break.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/codegen/criticalantidepbreaker-h/#l00046">46</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/codegen/criticalantidepbreaker-h">CriticalAntiDepBreaker.h</a>.

### Classes {#a4975f1bfbc77e749259af59eb3391485}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>std::vector&lt;const TargetRegisterClass &#42;&gt; llvm::CriticalAntiDepBreaker::Classes</>}>
For live regs that are only used in one register class in a live range, the register class.

If the register is not live, the corresponding value is null. If the register is live but used in multiple register classes, the corresponding value is -1 casted to a pointer.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/codegen/criticalantidepbreaker-h/#l00053">53</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/codegen/criticalantidepbreaker-h">CriticalAntiDepBreaker.h</a>.
